item.title: [WFLY-5335] Singleton deployment of EAR fails
item.description:
When trying to deploy our clustering test application "clusterbench" as a singleton deployment, server boot fails in an unrecoverable manner.

To identify clusterbench-ee7.ear as a singleton deployment, I added singleton-deployment.xml deployment descriptor into deployment /META-INF/ folder. The modified clusterbench-ee7.ear is attached.
The same issue occurs when trying with latest wildfly upstream/master bits.

Server logs:

customfieldvalues.customfieldvalue:
1. Get two copies of EAP 7.0.0.DR9, no configuration modification needed.
2. For both servers, copy cluterbench-ee7.ear (see attachments) to standalone/deployments folder.
3. Start both servers with standalone-ha profile:

Server 1 startup command

 
./bin/standalone.sh -c standalone-ha.xml -Djboss.node.name=node1

Server 2 startup command

 
./bin/standalone.sh -c standalone-ha.xml -Djboss.node.name=node2 -Djboss.socket.binding.port-offset=100

4. Check the server logs.
